parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks and Cooler Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks and cooler failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil filter housing assembly
oil cooler adapter housing
or intake manifold gasket; engine overheating; ticking or knocking noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty lifters can cause camshaft damage, engine misfires, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Ticking or knocking noises from the engine; engine misfires; camshaft damage; oil leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling; loss of power; fuel pump failure; sudden deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and failure can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling; engine failure; sudden loss of power; warning lights illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, damage, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
